        "prompt_sha256": "2d4310fa3fccc80df83366866208dac06cc88a96389b6305d5c6fb1104decb36",
        "transcript": "Was going to dress me, demanded Mary. Martha sat up on her heels again and stared. She spoke in broad Yorkshire in her amazement. Can a tha dress thy sen, she said. What do you mean? I don't understand your language, said Mary. Ay, I forgot, Martha said. Mrs. Medlock told me I'd have to be careful or you wouldn't know what I was sayin. I mean, can't you put on your own clothes? No, answered Mary, quite indignantly. I never did in my life. My Ayah dressed me, of course. Well, said Martha, evidently not in the least aware that she was impudent, it's time they should learn. They cannot begin younger. It'll do the good to wait on thy son a bit. My mother always said she couldn't see why grand people's children didn't turn out fair fools. What with nurses and being washed and dressed and took out to walk as if they was puppies. Please. Thank you.",
